sql:
SELECT AVG(execution_time) AS average_execution_time
FROM jobs
WHERE status = 'running';

external_knowledge:
- 'demanding tasks' refers to jobs with high resource requirements;
- 'high importance' corresponds to jobs marked as 'high' priority;
- 'consumed more than the usual amount of resources' indicates an average resource usage greater than 100 units.

sql:
SELECT execution_status, AVG(execution_time) AS average_execution_time
FROM job_execution
GROUP BY execution_status;

SELECT AVG(execution_time) AS average_execution_time
FROM job_execution
WHERE execution_status = 'completed';

SELECT DISTINCT j.job_id, j.status AS job_status
FROM jobs j
JOIN job_execution je ON j.job_id = je.job_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS completed_jobs_count
FROM jobs
WHERE status = 'completed';

external_knowledge:
- Processors are likened to sailing ships embarking on voyages (jobs).;
- Allocation and deallocation times represent the mooring and unmooring of these ships.;
- The total allocated time is the duration the ship was at sea (processed jobs).;
- The total executed time signifies the time spent actively navigating (executing jobs).;
- Each voyage (job) is a completed task by the ship (processor).;
